               <msContents>
                  <summary>Untitled Persian translation and epitome of an Arabic theological
                     treatise on the thousand and one ‘beautiful names’ of Allāh, with numerological
                     details, by an unnamed translator.</summary>
                  <msItem class="https://lccn.loc.gov/gf2015026087 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85106123"
                     n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_87-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled Persian translation and epitome of an Arabic theological
                           treatise on the thousand and one ‘beautiful names’ of Allāh, with
                           numerological details, by an unnamed translator. </p>
                        <p>The original Arabic treatise was commissioned for the benefit of
                           creation, following the conquest of Nishapur, by <persName
                              key="person_f8266" role="oth">Sulṭān Saʿīd ibn Sulṭān Maḥmūd
                              Ghāzī</persName>, and compiled over the course of a year in
                           consultation with several eminent scholars, <persName key="viaf_68980610"
                              role="ctb">Abū al-Qāsim al-Qushayrī</persName>, <persName
                              key="person_f8267" role="ctb">Qāz̤ī Muḥammad Nāṣiḥī</persName>,
                              <persName key="person_f8268" role="ctb">Qāz̤ī Ṣāʿid</persName>,
                              <persName key="person_f8269" role="ctb">Abū Naṣr Ṣābūnī</persName>,
                              <persName key="person_f8270" role="ctb">Khvājah Suhayl</persName>,
                              <persName key="person_f8271" role="ctb">Abū Manṣūr Hiravī</persName>,
                              <persName key="person_f8272" role="ctb">Abī Sulaymān
                              Khiṭāʾī</persName>, <persName key="person_f8273" role="ctb">Abū
                              al-Faz̤l Karkhī</persName>, <persName key="person_f8274" role="ctb"
                              >Abū ʿAbd Allāh Shīrāzī</persName>, <persName key="person_f8275"
                              role="ctb">Abū Isḥāq Jamshīdī</persName> and others. The work was
                           eventually presented to the ‘Abbasid Caliph, <persName
                              key="viaf_160859953" role="rcp">Abū al-ʿAbbās Qādir Billāh</persName>. </p>
                        <p>The colophon date placed at the end of the preface (f. 2r), stating the
                           year 911/1505-6, has probably been copied verbatim from the older source
                           manuscript; datable to the late eighteenth century. </p>
                        <p>Nastaʿlīq tending to shikastah āmīz. </p>
                        <p>Folios bound; creased, stained, and cropped. </p>
                     </note>
